To better understand the point spread functions (PSF) delivered by the SCAO system, we first have a look at the structure of the ELT PSF in Fig. 22. The segmented primary mirror of the ELT together with the spiders that hold the secondary mirror determine the basic PSF that the telescope can deliver. Any high-contrast imaging device has to take that into account. For our simulations, this is reflected in the used pupil mask as outlined in Section 5.4.
